ey grow too close together  they become thin and sickly and never obtain maximum growth. We need room to grow.', 47088, 0), (406738, 'We cannot hold a torch to light another''s path without brightening our own.', 11160, 0), (406739, 'What I spent  is gone  what I kept  I lost  but what I gave away will be mine forever.', 64174, 0), (406740, 'In helping others  we shall help ourselves  for whatever good we give out completes the circle and comes back to us.', 64309, 0), (406741, 'An act of goodness is of itself an act of happiness.', 2006, 0), (406742, 'My happiness derives from knowing the people I love are happy.', 64310, 0), (406743, 'There is nothing to make you like other human beings so much as doing things for them.', 751, 0), (406744, 'Happiness ... is achieved only by making others happy.', 64187, 0), (406745, 'The most infectiously joyous men and women are those who forget themselves in thinking about others and serving others.', 23094, 0), (406746, 'Giving opens the way for receiving.', 60287, 0), (406747, 'Fill the cup of happiness for others  and there will be enough overflowing to fill yours to the brim.', 64308, 0), (406748, 'Nothing liberates our greatness like the desire to help  the desire to serve.', 534, 0), (406749, 'He that will not permit his wealth to do any good for others ... cuts himself off from the truest pleasure here and the highest happiness later.', 432, 0), (406750, 'The closer I''m bound in love to you  the closer I am to free.', 64311, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (406751, 'True religion ... is giving and finding one''s happiness by bringing happiness into the lives of others.', 62367, 0), (406752, 'Power is the ability to do good things for others.', 64312, 0), (406753, 'If you give your life as a wholehearted response to love  then love will wholeheartedly respond to you.', 534, 0), (406754, 'Pleasure is a reciprocal  no one feels it who does not at the same time give it. To be pleased  one must please.', 62413, 0), (406755, 'When their children flourish  almost all mothers have a sense of well-being.', 64313, 0), (406756, 'If we had no regard for others'' feelings or fortune  we would grow cold and indifferent to life itself.', 62529, 0), (406757, 'To devote a portion of one''s leisure to doing something for someone else is one of the highest forms of recreation.', 64314, 0), (406758, 'Live for thy neighbor if thou wouldst live for thyself.', 62237, 0), (406759, 'The true way to soften one''s troubles is to solace those of others.', 64173, 0), (406760, 'Anything done for another is done for oneself.', 64315, 0), (406761, 'What we frankly give  forever is our own.', 62877, 0), (406762, 'Every charitable act is a stepping stone toward heaven.', 2175, 0), (406763, 'The human being who lives only for himself finally reaps nothing but unhappiness. Selfishness corrodes. Unselfishness ennobles  satisfies. Don''t put off the joy derivable from doing helpful  kindly things for others.', 14130, 0), (406764, 'There is no exercise better for the heart than reaching down and lifting people up.', 28728, 0), (406765, 'Goodness is the only investment that never fails.', 1049, 0), (406766, 'Help your brother''s boat across  and your own will reach the shore.', 62549, 0), (406767, 'Be unselfish.... If you think of yourself only  you cannot develop because you are choking the source of development  which is spiritual expansion through thought for others.', 62808, 0), (406768, 'An effort made for the happiness of others lifts us above ourselves.', 59119, 0), (406769, 'Happiness ... consists in giving  and in serving others.', 45086, 0), (406770, 'Try to forget yourself in the service of others. For when we think too much of ourselves and our own interests  we easily become despondent. But when we work for others  our efforts return to bless us.', 64316, 0), (406771, 'Doing good is the only certainly happy action of a man''s life.', 63457, 0), (406772, 'The greatest happiness in the world is to make others happy.', 3603, 0), (406773, 'We make a living by what we get  but we make a life by what we give.', 63548, 0), (406774, 'You may not have saved a lot of money in your life  but if you have saved a lot of heartaches for other folks  you are a pretty rich man.', 64317, 0), (406775, 'Only a life lived for others is a life worth while.', 104, 0), (406776, 'Unless we give part of ourselves away  unless we can live with other people and understand them and help them  we are missing the most essential part of our own lives.', 64318, 0), (406777, 'To complain that life has no joys while there is a single creature whom we can relieve by our bounty  assist by our counsels or enliven by our presence  is to lament the loss of that which we possess  and is just as rational as to die of thirst with the cup in our hands.', 63812, 0), (406778, 'If you have not often felt the joy of doing a kind act  you have neglected much  and most of all yourself.', 64182, 0), (406779, 'As the purse is emptied  the heart is filled.', 98, 0), (406780, 'Goodwill to others ... helps build you up. It is good for your body. It makes your blood purer  your muscles stronger  and your whole form more symmetrical in shape. It is the real elixir of life.', 48875, 0), (406781, 'Set about doing good to somebody. Put on your hat and go and visit the sick and poor of your neighborhood  inquire into their circumstances and minister to their wants. Seek out the desolate and afflicted and oppressed ... I have often tried this method  and have always found it the best medicine for a heavy heart.', 33, 0), (406782, 'We grow by love ... others are our nutriment.', 3573, 0), (406783, 'When you learn to live for others  they will live for you.', 2055, 0), (406784, 'No man is more cheated than the selfish man.', 2175, 0), (406785, 'In about the same degree as you are helpful  you will be happy.', 64176, 0), (406786, 'He that despiseth his neighbor sin-neth  but he that hath mercy on the poor  happy is he.', 5587, 0), (406787, 'The most exquisite pleasure is giving pleasure to others.', 5879, 0), (406788, 'Happiness is a by-product of an effort to make someone else happy.', 64319, 0), (406789, 'The fragrance of what you give away stays with you.', 64320, 0), (406790, 'Life becomes harder for us when we live for others  but it also becomes richer and happier.', 1006, 0), (406791, 'Sow good services  sweet remembrances will grow from them.', 62704, 0), (406792, 'We all of us need assistance. Those who sustain others themselves want to be sustained.', 64321, 0), (406793, 'When you cease to make a contribution  you begin to die.', 141, 0), (406794, 'To help all created things  that is the measure of our responsibility  to be helped by all  that is the measure of our hope.', 64322, 0), (406795, 'Those who bring sunshine to the lives of others cannot keep it from themselves.', 63085, 0), (406796, 'When one''s own problems are unsolvable and all best efforts are frustrated  it is lifesaving to listen to other people''s problems.', 34589, 0), (406797, 'The best way to cheer yourself is to try to cheer somebody else up.', 286, 0), (406798, 'There is no happiness in having or in getting  but only in giving.', 45086, 0), (406799, 'Do things for others and you''ll find your self-consciousness evaporating like morning dew.', 1005, 0), (406800, 'There remain times when one can only endure. One lives on  one doesn''t die  and the only thing that one can do  is to fill one''s