iples are involved  as a rule the majority are wrong.', 10499, 0), (406933, 'More history''s made by secret handshakes than by battles  bills and proclamations.', 17445, 0), (406934, 'History  n: an account mostly false  of events  mostly unimportant  which are brought about by rulers  mostly knaves  and soldiers  mostly fools.', 224, 0), (406935, 'The historical sense involves a perception  not only of the pastness of the past  but of its presence.', 1067, 0), (406936, 'Truth is the only merit that gives dignity and worth to history.', 63500, 0), (406937, 'History is more or less bunk.', 1796, 0), (406938, 'I have no history but the length of my bones.', 64344, 0), (406939, 'History is a pact between the dead  the living  and the yet unborn.', 2026, 0), (406940, 'A people without history is like wind on the buffalo grass.', 64345, 0), (406941, 'The function of posterity is to look after itself.', 300, 0), (406942, 'The world''s history is constant  like the laws of nature  and simple  like the souls of men. The same conditions continually produce the same results.', 62336, 0), (406943, 'History is just the portrayal of crimes and misfortunes.', 808, 0), (406944, 'We should keep the Panama Canal. After all we stole it fair and square.', 64346, 0), (406945, 'The history of things that didn''t happen has never been written.', 2393, 0), (406946, 'The memories of men are too frail a thread to hang history from.', 64347, 0), (406947, 'The rich experience of history teaches that up to now not a single class has voluntarily made way for another class.', 11422, 0), (406948, 'Dictators ride to and fro on tigers from which they dare not dismount. And the tigers are getting hungry.', 3621, 0), (406949, 'History is something that never happened  written by a man who wasn''t there.', 33, 0), (406950, 'History  a distillation of rumor', 3061, 0);
